 constellations by ostensibly subverting the boundaries inscribed by caste hierarchy. Stephanie Stocker explores how these friendships are maintained in wider social contexts, finding that the actors engage in supportive networks throughout career and marriage events. Instead of assuming these relationships to be of an entirely different, `alternative category', however, Stocker's study proposes a dynamic character of friendship which in fact remains in conjunction with Indian values of hierarchy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCastezIndiazMadurai. 0aFriendshipzIndiazMadurai. 0aGraduate studentszIndiazMadurai. 0aMarriagezIndiazMadurai. 0aMiddle classzIndiazMadurai. 4aAsia. 4aCulture. 4aEducation. 4aEthnology. 4aFriendship. 4aIndia. 4aLifestyle. 4aMarriage. 4aSociology of Culture. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aAsia.  aCulture.  aEducation.  aEthnology.  aFriendship.  aIndia.  aLifestyle.  aMarriage.  aSociology of Culture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2017z9783110548242oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUrban Studies and Social Rights eBook Package PP 2016-2019z978311063851608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Contemporary eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311066154540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839438855zCo-access DOI >>